The paper focuses on automated techniques for functional GUI testing of mobile applications, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses model-checking, symbolic execution, constraint solving, and search-based test generation, which are techniques commonly used in programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also touches on security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it discusses the effectiveness of testing techniques. Finally, the paper discusses the practicality of testing techniques, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
